     In this work, ZS-DeconvNet models were trained on a PC with an Intel Core i7-11700 processor and an RTX 3090 graphic processing card (NVIDIA) under the software environment of TensorFlow 2.5.0 and python 3.9.7. Before training, the paired input/GT images were first augmented into several patch pairs via random cropping, horizontal/vertical flipping and rotation transformation to further enrich the training dataset, which eventually generated ~20,000 pairs of 2D patches (128




